title: Parametrized tube
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The //parametrized tube// around a space curve $$\gamma$$ of radius $$r>0$$ corresponding to an adapted frame field $$T,N,B$$ is given by

$$\begin{gathered}
f\colon [0,L] \times [0,2\pi] \to \R^3,\\
f(t,\phi) \coloneqq \gamma(t) + r\cos(\phi)N + r\sin(\phi)B.
\end{gathered}$$

If the normal field is parallel, the coordinate lines are orthogonal.